paidPrice.description: The paid price from the customer perspective. Matches the sum of the trips price with all the fees

rawPrice.description: The actual price from Tictactrip's perspective. Matches the sum of the trips price without any fees.

code.description: The discount card number. Matches the `discountCardId` in TTT's DB

id.description: Matches the TTT discount card ID's

partnerExternalId.description: Matches an id provided from a partner. It is used to keep track of the partner's orders and enables an order match between their system and our own

minNbSteps.description: minimum number of segments for the origin-destination

nbPerDay.description: number of trips per day in average

cities.description: array with the intermediate cities' full name

departureTsOfLast.description: timestamp of the last departure expressed in minutes (08:00 => 8*60 => 480)

departureTsOfFirst.description: timestamp of the first departure expressed in minutes (08:00 => 8*60 => 480)

isCancellable.description: Specifies whether the booking is cancellable or not

feeCents.description: The fee in cents that applies to the cancellation and must be deducted from the price to calculate the refund value

cutoff.description: The date (deadline) in ISO 8601 format by which the booking can be cancelled for a cost of `feeCents`. e.g. 2021-06-15T06:05:00.000Z

isRefundedByVoucher.description: Specifies whether the booking is reimbursed with coupons or not

Partial_ICancellationStatusPayload_.description: Make all properties in T optional

Partial_IPartner_.description: Make all properties in T optional

post.description: Fetch results. Ignore search request that are further than 1800KM.

get.description: Get a cart by its id and its matching order if it exists.

patch.description:
Updates a cart with the provided informations. A price lookup is done everytime a cart is patched.
Keep in mind that patching a cart with an empty payload WILL NOT reset the cart's data, and will trigger a price lookup with the saved cart's data.

400.description: If trip does not exist or has expired

value.errorMessage: The trip does not exist or has expired

post.description: Creates a cart. Has to contain at least an outbound trip id and minimal passenger information for it to work.

get.description: Retrieves the order from the given cart ID.

post.description:
Creates an order. It uses the cart's information to build the order from it.
The cart must have been patched with customer information and at least one passenger.
